Yeah, Java doesn't do multimethods (i.e., method dispatch based on runtime argument types).<p>If Class X has two methods:<p><pre><code>  void foo(Object i);
  void foo(Integer i);
</code></pre>
then:<p><pre><code>  Object test = new Integer(4);
  X x = new X();
  x.foo(test);
</code></pre>
will invoke 'void foo(Object o);' based on the compile time type of test.<p>Java does do dispatch based on the runtime type of X - but it is quite limiting once you are used to having proper multiple dispatch at your disposal.<p>(caveat: not in front of a javac - this is from memory).
